1
00:01:31,180 --> 00:01:35,000
[The Lost National Treasure]

2
00:01:35,050 --> 00:01:37,880
[Episode 21]

3
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:41,150
If one project is enough to wear you out,

4
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:42,710
then I suggest

5
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,570
you might as well

6
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,259
go back to the institute
and do a desk job.

7
00:01:47,550 --> 00:01:49,210
Wouldn't that be much easier?

8
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:57,400
Though you'd lose fieldwork subsidies,

9
00:01:58,229 --> 00:01:59,400
you could marry me.

10
00:02:00,170 --> 00:02:02,020
You don't like eating much anyway.

11
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:03,120
Once I'm officially employed,

12
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,840
my salary should be enough to support you.

13
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,330
What do you think?

14
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:06,510
Are you crazy?

15
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:07,480
Who wants to marry you?

16
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,110
Murdering your husband.

17
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:09,870
You'd be dead the moment you marry me.

18
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:11,070
I’d beat you to death.

19
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:11,910
Shut up!

20
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:13,840
Ancestors, please show your divine power.

21
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,000
Come and testify for me,

22
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,140
or at least be a witness.

23
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,340
You can't mess with

24
00:02:23,370 --> 00:02:25,370
women who do field archaeology.

25
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:27,550
They're stronger than mules.

26
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,020
Who are you calling a mule?

27
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,290
I’m telling you,

28
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,079
it’s only because I haven’t eaten today.

29
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:32,900
Otherwise, you'd

30
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,310
already be in an ambulance.

31
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:35,520
Are you sure, Luo Qing?

32
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,520
Why don't you try?

33
00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:41,550
Here, I’ve got a piece of chocolate.

34
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:42,450
Eat it.

35
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,930
Let’s see if I end up in the ER today.

36
00:02:47,050 --> 00:02:47,510
Come on.

37
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,050
You still don’t believe me?

38
00:02:58,910 --> 00:03:01,170
Who eats chocolate when they're hungry?

39
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,840
Next time, remember to bring a roujiamo.

40
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,590
Fine, if you want roujiamo,

41
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:06,790
I’ll stuff myself inside it if I have to.

42
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:13,120
Is it dry?

43
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,620
I'll bring you a bowl of chicken soup.

44
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,829
There’s a saying,

45
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:25,480
no plan is ever perfect,

46
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:28,200
but your determination can be.

47
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,600
The best plan you can think of right now,

48
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,560
that’s already the best one.

49
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:37,520
Sometimes, completion is more important
than perfection.

50
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,940
Even if you screw it up,

51
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,079
so what?

52
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,430
You've done your best.

53
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,280
If you're wrong, it won't matter.

54
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,470
You’ve got

55
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:46,470
Mrs. Zan and Director Zhang backing you.

56
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:46,870
Right?

57
00:03:47,329 --> 00:03:48,079
Even if

58
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:49,960
you smash the ancestors' skulls,

59
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:52,270
you’d still have Mr. Zan.

60
00:03:53,079 --> 00:03:55,210
What are you afraid of? We're all here.

61
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:55,750
Right?

62
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,090
Alright.

63
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,040
Eat up and get to bed.

64
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,570
Once you wake up, it’s a new day.

65
00:06:32,230 --> 00:06:34,270
Jianhui, no matter how much you drink,
you’ll be fine.

66
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:34,720
It doesn’t get you drunk.

67
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,370
Yeah, Jianhui.
This wine’s over thirty years old.

68
00:06:36,370 --> 00:06:37,980
It does have a smooth taste.

69
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:38,630
But,

70
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:40,860
there's a hint of Chinese herbal medicine.

71
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:42,520
Maybe it’s been aged too long.

72
00:07:42,310 --> 00:07:43,570
What's wrong with you?

73
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,610
Driving so fast.

74
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:47,670
Trying to reincarnate or what?

75
00:07:47,670 --> 00:07:48,560
You’re nuts.

76
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:50,830
You’ll have a crash sooner or later.

77
00:08:22,410 --> 00:08:22,980
Wen Wen.

78
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:28,720
Wen Wen.

79
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,000
Wen Wen.

80
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:06,330
I'm not that kind of sleazy person.

81
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:07,850
There was something wrong with the wine.

82
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:09,780
Liu Shusheng set us up.

83
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:35,060
Sorry!

84
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,330
The number you have dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

85
00:11:13,810 --> 00:11:15,470
What time are you coming over?

86
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,270
Call me back when you wake up.

87
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,730
You’re here.

88
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:05,570
-Guang.
-Brother.

89
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,200
What brings you here?

90
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,650
Just passing by.

91
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:10,360
So I came to see you.

92
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:16,840
How’s the place?

93
00:12:17,510 --> 00:12:18,170
It's great.

94
00:12:19,670 --> 00:12:21,000
Have you been drinking?

95
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,010
Had a few drinks last night.

96
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,750
Don't drink so much.

97
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:26,270
It's not good for your health.

98
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,790
I can still smell it now.

99
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:29,320
Brother.

100
00:12:29,810 --> 00:12:31,640
Wen Wen must still be asleep.

101
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:33,890
She hasn’t picked up all morning.

102
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,550
She went with your sister-in-law.

103
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,550
The signal's poor in the mountains.

104
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,390
I see.

105
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,460
She said she was going to pick up
the photos yesterday,

106
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:43,460
but still hasn’t brought them back.

107
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:45,480
I’ll go get them later.

108
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,140
No need. I’ll get them for you.

109
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,500
There's an urgent job.

110
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:50,000
You need to go out of Qinchuan.

111
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,060
Give me your phone.

112
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:52,930
Go out of Qinchuan?

113
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,270
Get a new SIM card when you get there.

114
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:58,880
Don't let anyone know
you're coming from Qinchuan.

115
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:01,480
Do I need to leave now?

116
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:03,730
Yes, the goods are urgently needed.

117
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,390
Pack your things.

118
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,320
Okay.

119
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:12,770
Go ahead.

120
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:13,870
Mr. Guo. Mr. Fang.

121
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,630
We've discovered two tomb passages so far.

122
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:17,750
The east one is the longest.

123
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:19,480
It's 134.5 meters long.

124
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,860
The narrowest part is 9.7 meters.

125
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,600
The widest part is 40.2 meters.

126
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,270
So wide?

127
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,460
If it isn't a feudal prince's tomb,

128
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:28,440
it has to be at least
a marquis-level tomb.

129
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,360
Could it be Princess Guantao's tomb?

130
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:30,870
Guo.

131
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,650
You're the Captain now.

132
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,040
A lot of people listen to you.

133
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,730
You’ve got to be
responsible for what you say.

134
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,840
Be cautious and don’t make wild guesses.

135
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,080
How can I be cautious?

136
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,080
The scale of this tomb
is right here for all to see.

137
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:45,190
All we've done is hit the edge

138
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,710
and found two passageways.

139
00:13:46,710 --> 00:13:50,510
We don’t even know if it’s a Zhong-shaped
tomb or a Ya-shaped one yet.

140
00:13:50,660 --> 00:13:51,190
Alright.

141
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:52,890
Let's continue exploring.

142
00:13:52,890 --> 00:13:53,340
Okay.

143
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:17,000
Oh, my land.

144
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:19,280
Captain Guo.

145
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:20,550
Smells good, huh?

146
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:21,520
It's delicious!

147
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,200
You scared me to death!

148
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:24,630
Mr. Lv.

149
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,480
How's Xiaoman doing?

150
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,240
Is her training completed?

151
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,040
Add a bit more.

152
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,000
I was just about to mention that.

153
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,270
Xiaoman is smart.

154
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,080
She's attentive and hardworking.

155
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:34,960
When she’s working,

156
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:37,000
she's no worse than us old technicians.

157
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:37,800
In my opinion,

158
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,200
with a bit more practice,

159
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,860
she could become a top expert.

160
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,160
That's right.

161
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:44,790
Captain Guo, didn't you hear that?

162
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:46,480
You should express your opinion quickly.

163
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,200
Xiaoman is so good.

164
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,200
If you don't recruit her soon,

165
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,630
someone else might snatch her up,

166
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:50,240
right?

167
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,370
Xiaoman.

168
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:54,350
Starting today,

169
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:57,030
you’re officially
the archaeological team's apprentice.

170
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,430
Twenty yuan a day.

171
00:14:58,780 --> 00:14:59,510
Is that okay?

172
00:14:59,550 --> 00:14:59,910
What?

173
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,360
What are you doing, Xiaoman?

174
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,490
Come on, thank them.

175
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,750
Thank you, Captain Guo.

176
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,610
Thank you, Kun.

177
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,360
Thank you, Mr. Lv.

178
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:10,440
I’ll work hard, I promise.

179
00:15:10,670 --> 00:15:12,240
Well, I never thought

180
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:12,960
that my girl

181
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:15,490
would find a job
in your archaeological team.

182
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:16,480
-Auntie
-It’s good.

183
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:17,960
We work with dirt all day,

184
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:20,290
not much different from what you folks do.

185
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:22,790
If Xiaoman does
anything wrong in the future

186
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:24,320
or doesn't listen, just let me know.

187
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,000
I'll talk to her.

188
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,870
Alright, no worries, it’s all good.

189
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:28,800
We haven't found anything bad yet.

190
00:15:30,490 --> 00:15:31,600
Uncle, have you eaten?

191
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,860
-I’ll get some for you.
-Uncle Youliang.

192
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:35,080
Fang.

193
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:36,270
Come here.

194
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,210
I’ll get it, Auntie.

195
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:42,270
The things I told you about,

196
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:44,130
why didn't you listen to any of it?

197
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:45,440
I told you not to ruin

198
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,640
other people's land.

199
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,080
But you went ahead

200
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:50,240
and messed it up from east to west.

201
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,270
What do you mean, Uncle?

202
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:52,080
What do I mean?

203
00:15:52,870 --> 00:15:54,600
Guo just had me look at his land.

204
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,390
You've ruined it.

205
00:15:56,410 --> 00:15:57,000
Guo?

206
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:58,870
Which one?

207
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,790
We've never even been to his land.

208
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:01,670
What nonsense is he talking about?

209
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:03,000
Guo is an honest man.

210
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,160
What's wrong with him?

211
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:06,480
Why would he make things up
and slander the archaeological team?

212
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,410
Uncle Youliang.

213
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,960
We coordinate every day
when we go out to survey.

214
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,150
There's no Guo as you mentioned.

215
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:12,810
We've never been to his place.

216
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:14,320
I work with
the archaeological team every day.

217
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,240
How could I not know?

218
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,440
Shut up. This has nothing to do with you.

219
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:20,910
Look at you.

220
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,790
Not listening to
your own daughter's words,

221
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:24,850
but believing outsiders' nonsense.

222
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,000
Fang.

223
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,290
Don't mind him. Come, let's eat.

224
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:30,510
Kun, let's eat, let's eat.

225
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:30,910
Okay.

226
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,120
Our plan is working well.

227
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:34,480
Right.

228
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,750
You bunch of idiots.

229
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,150
Idiots.

230
00:16:36,150 --> 00:16:37,030
You've ruined my land

231
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,030
like this.

232
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:39,030
How dare you come here?

233
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:39,670
W-What are you doing?

234
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:41,360
Let go of me. What are you pulling me for?

235
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,270
Look what you've done to the land.

236
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,870
And you still dare to come to my land?

237
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:45,320
Let go!

238
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:46,150
You're still trying to control me?

239
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,000
Who are you anyway?

240
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,240
Look what they've dug up.

241
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:48,670
Move.

242
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:49,960
Don't pull me!

243
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,150
Come and see, come on.

244
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:51,870
Come see what you've done!

245
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:52,440
Come here.

246
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:52,960
What are we looking at?

247
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:53,630
Look.

248
00:16:53,670 --> 00:16:55,130
Look at what you've dug up.

249
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,150
The archaeological team
need to watch this!

250
00:16:56,150 --> 00:16:57,630
Look at what you've done to the land.

251
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:58,890
Look, look here, here.

252
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:00,020
From east to west.

253
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,360
Look! Look! Look!

254
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:02,110
Uncle Guo.

255
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:03,990
This land wasn't dug up by us.

256
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:05,920
We never even entered
your land during our survey.

257
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:06,510
Exactly.

258
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:07,640
Show your evidence.

259
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:10,000
You said you haven't been to
Uncle Guo's land.

260
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,640
You've been to my land, haven't you?

261
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,240
My land has been dug up just like this.

262
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,349
It’s full of holes now.

263
00:17:14,349 --> 00:17:15,750
All my crops are ruined.

264
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:17,440
If it wasn't you, then who was it?

265
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,170
Impossible.

266
00:17:18,310 --> 00:17:18,790
We...

267
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:19,109
Impossible.

268
00:17:19,109 --> 00:17:21,119
We refilled all the exploration holes.

269
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,550
How could I have dug up your land?

270
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:23,069
I think you

271
00:17:23,069 --> 00:17:24,550
are just refusing to admit it now.

272
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:24,920
Let's go.

273
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,480
Let's go to my land
and confront each other.

274
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,030
You won't shed tears
until you see the coffin.

275
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:28,640
Follow me.

276
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:29,350
Let's go! Let's go!

277
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:30,590
Let's go.

278
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:32,170
Let's go to my land.

279
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:32,900
Let's go, let's go.

280
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:33,700
I'll show you.

281
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:36,880
