282
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:39,830
Look what you've done.

283
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:41,750
Look, look, look.

284
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:42,830
Take a good look.

285
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:43,590
Look at this land.

286
00:17:43,590 --> 00:17:44,650
Look at these pits.

287
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,930
Look around, look at this land.

288
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:48,830
No.

289
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,720
They're all big pits, one after another.

290
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,550
It wasn't us.

291
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:53,330
Didn't we refill them back?

292
00:17:53,330 --> 00:17:54,720
Yes, we didn't do this.

293
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:58,110
This pit is the biggest, come and see.

294
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,170
I'm furious, look.

295
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,000
The proof’s right there.

296
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,400
Nothing more to say, huh?

297
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:03,150
Uncle Guo.

298
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,310
We were drilling.

299
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,240
We filled the holes after drilling.

300
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,880
This really wasn't done by us.

301
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:08,920
You’re still denying it.

302
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,240
Even with the evidence
right in front of you.

303
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:11,750
If it wasn't you, then who was it?

304
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:12,830
It's like the ox doesn't
know its horns are curved,

305
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,070
the horse doesn't know its face is long.

306
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:15,750
I don't think you're
the archaeological team,

307
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:16,590
you're a demolition crew!

308
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:17,880
Watch your words.

309
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:19,440
We need evidence.

310
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,000
You keep asking for evidence.

311
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,000
The evidence should be your dog's name.

312
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,110
Evidence? You're standing on it.

313
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:24,770
How can you say that?

314
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:25,920
Still asking for evidence, huh?

315
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,510
You ruined someone’s land
and acted like nothing happened.

316
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:28,640
My land is ruined.

317
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,550
Only you have been to my land.

318
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,510
If it wasn't you,

319
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,400
then it was his dog.

320
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:32,960
Exactly.

321
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:37,070
We took photos
during our survey.

322
00:18:37,310 --> 00:18:39,170
We can use the photos as evidence.

323
00:18:40,590 --> 00:18:41,510
Photos?

324
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,000
Use the photos as evidence?

325
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:43,920
Right? Look.

326
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,200
We refilled them all back.

327
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,550
Put away that camera quickly.

328
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:47,000
Look.

329
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:48,460
See, this is the photo.

330
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:49,480
Look, we've done a good job.

331
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,790
Someone's been eating meat on the sly
and wiping their greasy mouth.

332
00:18:50,790 --> 00:18:51,960
Can you show me the bones?

333
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,110
Xian, Uncle.

334
00:18:53,130 --> 00:18:54,880
What’s going on this early in the morning?

335
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,240
What's going on here?

336
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,640
Look what you’ve done.

337
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,960
And you still have the nerve to ask?

338
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:01,750
How did the land end up like this?

339
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:03,680
If this was my land, I'd be angry too.

340
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:04,830
That's right, Fang Kun.

341
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:06,680
What did you promise me before?

342
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,200
You know I'm angry.

343
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,680
And you've dug up my land like this.

344
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:10,680
Xian, Xian, Xian.

345
00:19:11,110 --> 00:19:13,070
Our work method

346
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:14,620
is drilling holes,

347
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,270
Four centimeters per hole.

348
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:16,960
Have you seen it before?

349
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,000
I haven't. If you don't believe me,
go and see for yourselves.

350
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,310
Alright, this kind of thing.

351
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:21,550
Honestly, we wouldn't waste our time

352
00:19:21,550 --> 00:19:22,640
doing something like this.

353
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,920
Exactly, doing it this way
increases the workload.

354
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:25,720
That's right.

355
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,510
No matter what,

356
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:28,920
let's find someone

357
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,590
and get this land filled in first.

358
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:31,310
What do you think?

359
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,550
The problem is my crops are ruined.

360
00:19:32,550 --> 00:19:33,550
No. Why should we?

361
00:19:33,550 --> 00:19:34,830
Don't say anymore.

362
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:36,030
Why should we do that?

363
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:36,920
Right, right.

364
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:37,830
You're right.

365
00:19:37,830 --> 00:19:39,830
Even if we refill it,
the crops are ruined anyway, right?

366
00:19:39,830 --> 00:19:40,440
Okay.

367
00:19:41,070 --> 00:19:42,550
Xian, we've dealt with each other before.

368
00:19:42,550 --> 00:19:44,350
You know what kind of person I am.

369
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,720
Can you give us a little leeway here?

370
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:46,920
We’ll move fast

371
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,590
to figure out what really happened

372
00:19:48,590 --> 00:19:50,720
and work out a solution for you.

373
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:51,610
How about that?

374
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,160
So how long will it take?

375
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:55,270
As soon as possible.

376
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,350
As soon as possible, as soon as possible.

377
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:58,440
As soon as possible, as soon as possible.

378
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,790
That’s right, exactly.

379
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,480
Anyway, they can't run away.

380
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:02,260
Right.

381
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,170
This matter,

382
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:04,640
if it's not resolved,

383
00:20:05,030 --> 00:20:06,720
don't even think about
setting foot on our land.

384
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,510
That's right, don't even think about
entering our land.

385
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:09,910
Open the door, Youliang.

386
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:11,630
Open the door, open the door!

387
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,480
Open the door, open the door!

388
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,240
Open the door, open the door!

389
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,310
Honey.

390
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:23,960
Didn't you hear them

391
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,400
knocking on our door like that?

392
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,860
Aren't you going to do
something about this?

393
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:30,210
What does it have to do with me?

394
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,950
I told this group long ago

395
00:20:35,030 --> 00:20:36,830
not to ruin other people's land.

396
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,010
They didn't listen.

397
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,280
What now?

398
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:42,030
They have the ability to cause trouble

399
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:43,890
but not the ability to resolve it.

400
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,600
Now they come looking for me.

401
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,970
And they're all pointing their guns at me.

402
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,120
The people who ruined the land are back.

403
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,400
One at a time, speak one at a time.

404
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,660
I can't hear anything.

405
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,440
Speak one at a time.

406
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,680
Speak one at a time.

407
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:07,930
That's how it is.

408
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:11,310
You agreed to dig small holes at the time.

409
00:21:11,510 --> 00:21:11,860
Exactly.

410
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:14,550
Now you've dug big holes all over my land.

411
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,550
That's right.

412
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,720
What are you going to do about it?

413
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:22,160
No, your land is completely ruined.

414
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,090
It's all ruined.

415
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:24,920
There are big holes everywhere.

416
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,050
They're very large.

417
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,590
You're a grown man.

418
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,960
How can you be so narrow-minded?

419
00:21:32,110 --> 00:21:34,370
Why are you always picking on these kids?

420
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,590
If you don't handle this matter,

421
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:37,140
just wait and see.

422
00:21:37,140 --> 00:21:40,140
Your daughter will fight with you
when she comes back.

423
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,530
What's wrong with you two?

424
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,110
Always at odds with me.

425
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:47,040
What's the matter?

426
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:49,490
You're on the same side now?

427
00:21:50,090 --> 00:21:52,220
Whether you want to deal with it or not,

428
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:54,650
anything that happens in Yin Village

429
00:21:54,650 --> 00:21:55,330
will ultimately

430
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:57,060
fall on you as the Chief.

431
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:09,640
He's coming out, he's coming out.

432
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,790
The Chief is coming out.

433
00:22:10,790 --> 00:22:11,590
Chief, Chief.

434
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:14,040
Let me tell you, let me tell you.

435
00:22:14,110 --> 00:22:15,170
Alright, alright.

436
00:22:15,590 --> 00:22:16,920
Stop arguing, will you?

437
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,220
This matter is unclear right now.

438
00:22:19,220 --> 00:22:20,270
Everyone has their own side of the story.

439
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,590
Everyone thinks they're right.

440
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:22,350
Let's do this.

441
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,550
Let's go to the village committee
to find a witness, okay?

442
00:22:24,550 --> 00:22:25,070
Good.

443
00:22:25,270 --> 00:22:26,640
That works, that works.

444
00:22:30,510 --> 00:22:31,840
Quiet down, quiet down.

445
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,510
Today's matter

446
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:38,290
is mainly to resolve the issue
between the archaeological team

447
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:39,660
and our villagers.

448
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:42,310
The archaeological team

449
00:22:43,860 --> 00:22:44,990
claims they didn’t

450
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,440
ruin the land.

451
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:47,880
But there’s no way

452
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:48,960
we’d

453
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,960
ruin our own land,

454
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:50,440
right?

455
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,720
Exactly!

456
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,930
This isn’t hard to sort out.

457
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,680
Yan Shoucun

458
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,970
has been guarding the land.

459
00:22:58,010 --> 00:22:59,850
Heizui is very smart.

460
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:01,160
First,

461
00:23:01,590 --> 00:23:03,960
it definitely wouldn't bark at villagers.

462
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,560
Secondly,

463
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:08,350
it wouldn't bark at
the archaeological team members either.

464
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:10,480
That should make it easy to figure out.

465
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,200
It must have been done by outsiders.

466
00:23:14,030 --> 00:23:14,560
Shoucun,

467
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:19,080
can you tell us what's been happening
these past few days?

468
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:22,370
I don't know.

469
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,420
How can you not know?

470
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:27,360
Are your ears stuffed with donkey hair?

471
00:23:27,790 --> 00:23:29,510
Or has your Heizui gone mute?

472
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,240
You don’t even know
if the dogs have barked?

473
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:34,640
You can't be afraid of offending outsiders

474
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,960
and forget that

475
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:37,000
you're from Yin Village.

476
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,600
Anyway, these past few days,

477
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:39,920
Heizui hasn't made a single sound.

478
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,030
Uncle Shoucun, think carefully again.

479
00:23:42,030 --> 00:23:45,160
You must have been sleeping deeply
and haven't heard it.

480
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,070
I'm not a pig,

481
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:50,770
sleeping so deeply.

482
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,180
If Heizui barked once,

483
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:55,310
everyone on the plain would hear it.

484
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:57,030
When I sleep, his one ear is always up,

485
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:59,490
just waiting for bad guys
to come to the site.

486
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,310
Anyway, Heizui hasn't barked
these past few days.

487
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:02,400
I don't know about this.

488
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,270
I still need to go on patrol.

489
00:24:03,270 --> 00:24:03,810
Let's go, Heizui.

490
00:24:03,810 --> 00:24:04,830
You're just a pig.

491
00:24:04,830 --> 00:24:06,160
Yan Shoucun, come back.

492
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,200
Did you hear that?

493
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:10,850
Shoucun is honest.

494
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,210
He wouldn't talk nonsense.

495
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,280
No outsiders have been here.

496
00:24:15,590 --> 00:24:17,160
Then it must be your archaeological team.

497
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,790
That's right, no outsiders have been here.

498
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:21,000
Why do no outsiders
being here mean we did it?

499
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,000
Were we farting against the wind?

500
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,240
Digging up our own land ourselves?

501
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:24,960
Who knows?

502
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:25,510
What do you mean?

503
00:24:25,510 --> 00:24:26,200
What do you mean?

504
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,130
What do you mean?

505
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,270
What do you mean?

506
00:24:28,270 --> 00:24:28,720
Uncle Youliang.

507
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:29,480
You've gone too far.

508
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:29,920
Look.

509
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,900
We have photos of
our archaeological work every day.

510
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:32,900
This is evidence.

511
00:24:33,310 --> 00:24:33,910
Moreover,

512
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:36,200
we've been coming to Yin Village
for so many years, right?

513
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,270
Why would we dig up your land
at this critical moment?

514
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:39,070
It doesn't make sense, does it?

515
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:40,480
Look at those photos, right?

516
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,640
You took them.

517
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,240
You can show whatever you want.

518
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,790
What do you mean?

519
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:47,180
Can you take a photo while digging a hole?

520
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:48,960
Uncles. Aunties.

521
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,570
We're here today to solve the problem.

522
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,130
Let’s talk calmly.

523
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,480
Don’t get angry, okay?

524
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:56,410
Don't get angry.

525
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:58,720
I also grew up working in the fields.

526
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:01,160
I care about our crops more than anyone.

527
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:03,110
If the archaeological team
ruined the land,

528
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,240
how could I ignore it?

529
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:04,720
Right?

530
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:07,830
I swear to the City God,

531
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:11,310
