00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,070
Why is that?

560
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:03,770
Whoever’s wife it is, take her home.

561
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,170
Chief, Chief, calm down.

562
00:26:05,310 --> 00:26:06,200
Don't listen to her.

563
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,920
You are so troublesome.

564
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:10,850
The Chief is surely on our side, right?

565
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,240
Stop gnawing on that bun.

566
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,640
You say something first.

567
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,960
That archaeological team

568
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,260
and our villagers,

569
00:26:17,350 --> 00:26:19,550
we’re like a stick hitting a stove door.

570
00:26:19,550 --> 00:26:20,790
What are we here for today?

571
00:26:20,790 --> 00:26:21,590
Let's get to the point.

572
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:22,920
Stop talking nonsense.

573
00:26:24,270 --> 00:26:25,070
That's right.

574
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,440
Let's think about
how to solve this problem.

575
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:28,790
How do you suggest we solve it?

576
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:30,550
You're responsible for the land
you dug up.

577
00:26:30,550 --> 00:26:32,550
You're not offering any solutions.

578
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:33,070
Guo.

579
00:26:34,270 --> 00:26:35,960
You're an elder in our village.

580
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:36,720
We can't

581
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:39,680
let these youngsters make the decisions.

582
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:42,010
How should we handle this?

583
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,540
I’ll listen to you.

584
00:26:48,790 --> 00:26:49,850
Debts must be paid.

585
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:51,590
My land is ruined.

586
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,160
The cherry trees were planted for nothing.

587
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,220
Buying seedlings,

588
00:26:55,350 --> 00:26:56,150
fertilizing,

589
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,260
plowing, watering,

590
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:58,550
plus compensation for lost crops,

591
00:26:58,550 --> 00:27:00,480
labor costs, everything counted.

592
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:02,790
We're not trying to
take advantage of anyone.

593
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:04,270
Everyone should get their fair share.

594
00:27:04,270 --> 00:27:07,200
Exactly, I'm not looking to
profit from this either.

595
00:27:12,510 --> 00:27:13,790
How is this our fault?

596
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:14,400
That's right.

597
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:17,240
Don't be angry, don't be angry.

598
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:19,000
Everyone, listen to me, listen to me.

599
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,460
Sister.

600
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:22,240
Fang Kun, Shilin.

601
00:27:22,980 --> 00:27:25,270
You’ve spent quite some time
out on the plain too,

602
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:26,380
You've seen it with your own eyes.

603
00:27:26,380 --> 00:27:28,310
We farmers live off the land.

604
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:30,160
Those few acres of land have been ruined.

605
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,640
We'll starve next year.

606
00:27:32,810 --> 00:27:33,790
Fellow villagers.

607
00:27:33,790 --> 00:27:34,240
Well.

608
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:37,680
The archaeological team
is like a guest in my home.

609
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,170
They're reasonable people.

610
00:27:39,170 --> 00:27:40,920
Well, how much land did they ruin?

611
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,400
They should compensate us accordingly.

612
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:42,800
Right?

613
00:27:43,070 --> 00:27:43,670
Uncle Guo.

614
00:27:44,940 --> 00:27:47,270
Five thousand yuan should be fair, right?

615
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,270
That's about right.

616
00:27:49,270 --> 00:27:50,130
Five thousand.

617
00:27:51,830 --> 00:27:52,750
Five thousand.

618
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:53,440
Five thousand.

619
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,070
You, that's enough.

620
00:27:55,420 --> 00:27:56,880
After all this time,

621
00:27:57,030 --> 00:27:58,790
it's just a self-directed play.

622
00:27:58,790 --> 00:27:59,590
What do you mean?

623
00:27:59,590 --> 00:28:00,520
What do you mean?

624
00:28:00,550 --> 00:28:01,830
What do you mean? What play?

625
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:02,720
You're trying to pin the blame

626
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:04,320
on our archaeological team.

627
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:06,770
Putting on this act just to extort money.

628
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,750
Who’s extorting your money?

629
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:10,350
Who’s extorting your money?

630
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,440
Who’s extorting your money?

631
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,700
We wouldn’t ruin land just to make money.

632
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,710
Whoever’s responsible
should take the blame.

633
00:28:19,060 --> 00:28:20,390
Bring out the evidence.

634
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:22,450
Let’s speak with evidence.

635
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:24,750
Kun.

636
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:25,610
Don't come out.

637
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:26,830
Come here.

638
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:27,870
Come here.

639
00:29:03,310 --> 00:29:05,350
We've known Fang Kun
and the others for years.

640
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:06,110
For years!

641
00:29:06,530 --> 00:29:08,750
Do they seem like the type
to do something like this?

642
00:29:08,750 --> 00:29:09,790
I don’t care about all that!

643
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:10,750
You don’t care about anything?

644
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:11,750
I'm not that free.

645
00:29:12,790 --> 00:29:14,240
Why should I care about this?

646
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,920
Didn't you hear what the villagers said?

647
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,750
They're saying we've taken some benefits
from the archaeological team.

648
00:29:18,750 --> 00:29:20,750
If I don't take that oil bottle,
I won't get my hands dirty.

649
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:21,080
Okay.

650
00:29:21,350 --> 00:29:22,000
Let me tell you,

651
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,680
as long as these folks
don’t stay in our house,

652
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:24,920
we won’t get that kind of gossip.

653
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,590
Do you know what this is called?

654
00:29:26,590 --> 00:29:27,680
Putting on makeup
before going to the coffin.

655
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:28,720
Wanting respect even when you're dead.

656
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:31,110
You’re afraid a stalk of lamp grass
on your back might crush you.

657
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:33,350
Xiaoman, why are you talking to
Dad like that?

658
00:29:33,350 --> 00:29:35,070
Dad, don't stoop to her level.

659
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,090
-Xiaoman.
-Get out!

660
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,130
Stop stirring up trouble here.

661
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:41,290
Hearing you annoys me so much.

662
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,000
[Yin Village]

663
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,510
If they don't let us stay, we won't stay.

664
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:50,750
If we're not welcome here,
we'll be welcome elsewhere.

665
00:29:50,750 --> 00:29:52,030
We have plenty of places to stay.

666
00:29:52,030 --> 00:29:53,830
But what good is
living in a five-star hotel?

667
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:56,160
What can you do
if they don't let you into the fields?

668
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,960
Then let
the district government coordinate.

669
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,530
I can't stand this humiliation.

670
00:29:59,530 --> 00:30:00,680
Guo, I'm not saying this to be mean,

671
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,010
your temper right now...

672
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:02,420
What?

673
00:30:03,030 --> 00:30:04,310
The things you just said to Uncle Guo,

674
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:05,810
I think you went a bit too far.

675
00:30:05,810 --> 00:30:07,480
Look how upset you made Uncle Guo.

676
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,940
He didn't seem to be lying.

677
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:10,680
Xiaoman might be right.

678
00:30:11,110 --> 00:30:13,660
No farmer would ruin their own land
for no reason.

679
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:16,160
Maybe there’s really something fishy
going on here.

680
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:17,160
Mr. Fang. Mr. Guo.

681
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:19,350
I have an idea,

682
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,110
just throwing it out there,

683
00:30:22,110 --> 00:30:24,240
It's up to you whether to listen or not.

684
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:27,590
When we were drilling
the Du Mausoleum before,

685
00:30:27,590 --> 00:30:28,850
some things happened.

686
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,240
Some local villagers,

687
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:32,550
seeing our archaeological team

688
00:30:32,550 --> 00:30:34,950
dig up quite a few brick
and tile fragments.

689
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,680
They heard

690
00:30:36,830 --> 00:30:38,880
that Qin bricks and Han tiles
can be sold for money.

691
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:39,940
So they got greedy.

692
00:30:40,110 --> 00:30:43,440
They sneaked into the land at night
to steal tile fragments.

693
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:47,480
I guess you're right, Lu.

694
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:50,110
I just took a close look at that land.

695
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:52,600
There are indeed obvious signs of digging.

696
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:53,680
I guess someone

697
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,540
was looking for something there.

698
00:30:55,640 --> 00:30:57,270
Then let's catch

699
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:59,530
those who are digging illegally, right?

700
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:02,790
It seems our archaeological team

701
00:31:02,790 --> 00:31:06,250
will have to play the role of
Relics Inspection Team this time.

702
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:06,920
How many did you dig?

703
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,190
Got two, two.

704
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:13,880
Lai.

705
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:15,480
Lai, look.

706
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:17,950
Finders keepers, right?

707
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,070
What are you doing?

708
00:32:23,070 --> 00:32:23,800
Who's there?

709
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,300
Don't move!

710
00:32:26,590 --> 00:32:27,190
Don't run!

711
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:27,770
Who is it?

712
00:32:28,140 --> 00:32:28,720
Put it down!

713
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:29,380
Put it down!

714
00:32:32,750 --> 00:32:33,750
Ouch, ouch, ouch!

715
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:35,310
It hurts, it hurts!

716
00:32:48,830 --> 00:32:50,550
You good-for-nothing!

717
00:32:50,890 --> 00:32:51,940
You little thief!

718
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:10,370
What's going on?

719
00:33:13,660 --> 00:33:14,660
What happened?

720
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,510
You're chasing away
the archaeological team?

721
00:33:17,510 --> 00:33:19,640
This was all your son-in-law's doing.

722
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:25,120
What's going on, Lai?

723
00:33:25,510 --> 00:33:28,240
I just dug up a few acres
of our village's own land.

724
00:33:28,310 --> 00:33:29,790
You dug up the land?

725
00:33:30,310 --> 00:33:31,880
Didn't you know this is illegal?

726
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:33,110
I didn't know!

727
00:33:33,110 --> 00:33:34,350
You got yourself into this mess.

728
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:35,350
You deal with it yourself.

729
00:33:35,350 --> 00:33:35,720
Dad!

730
00:33:35,790 --> 00:33:36,550
Take him away.

731
00:33:36,550 --> 00:33:37,590
Dad, I'm sorry!

732
00:33:37,610 --> 00:33:38,680
Xiaoman, I'm sorry!

733
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:40,480
How could you do such a thing?

734
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:41,890
I only dug this one time!

735
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,210
I didn't know!

736
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,880
T-This can't be dug up!

737
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:45,720
This, this...

738
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:47,760
Dacang, please spare me this time.

739
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,270
Please spare me this time.

740
00:33:49,270 --> 00:33:50,240
I won't dare do it again!

741
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:50,770
Xiaoman!

742
00:33:51,110 --> 00:33:52,960
Xiaoman, please beg Dacang for mercy!

743
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,480
The kid’s still young.

744
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,880
Don't mention me and the child.

745
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:55,720
I feel sick.

746
00:33:56,270 --> 00:33:57,550
What have you done?

747
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:58,750
I’m ashamed.

748
00:33:58,820 --> 00:34:00,580
Very ashamed.

749
00:34:02,530 --> 00:34:04,760
What have you done, Lai?

750
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:08,370
I’m so ashamed.

751
00:34:18,840 --> 00:34:20,239
That’s it. Take him away.

752
00:34:20,900 --> 00:34:21,360
No!

753
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:22,699
No, don't rush!

754
00:34:23,830 --> 00:34:24,699
This thing?

755
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,030
The land belongs to our family.

756
00:34:27,030 --> 00:34:28,030
The things belong to our family.

757
00:34:28,030 --> 00:34:29,480
This is all ours, right?

758
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,030
How is this breaking any law?

759
00:34:31,030 --> 00:34:31,840
Alright.

760
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:33,960
Stop shouting.

761
00:34:35,510 --> 00:34:37,040
Take care of things at home.

762
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,120
Comrade, let's go.

763
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:41,489
Let's go.

764
00:34:42,630 --> 00:34:44,710
W-Where are you taking him?

765
00:34:45,150 --> 00:34:46,400
This isn't illegal!

766
00:34:46,420 --> 00:34:47,630
I was digging on our own land!

767
00:34:47,630 --> 00:34:49,690
I didn't go dig anywhere else, right?

768
00:34:55,550 --> 00:34:56,030
Chief.

769
00:34:59,150 --> 00:35:00,810
Did we do the wrong thing here?

770
00:35:03,100 --> 00:35:04,500
We can't say we did wrong.

771
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:06,150
If

772
00:35:06,590 --> 00:35:08,880
you had chosen to settle things
peacefully at the time

773
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,480
and just paid the villagers,

774
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:13,150
those thieves wouldn’t have been caught,

775
00:35:13,150 --> 00:35:15,950
and the cultural relics
would keep disappearing.

776
00:35:16,370 --> 00:35:18,120
And the villagers' land

777
00:35:18,150 --> 00:35:18,840
would also

778
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,600
suffer some damage.

779
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,110
By then,

780
00:35:22,260 --> 00:35:22,790
even if we

781
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:24,840
use up all the savings our institute
has accumulated over the years,

782
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:27,840
we still can't compensate
for all the village's land.

783
00:35:28,510 --> 00:35:29,190
However,

784
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:30,480
this time

785
00:35:31,150 --> 00:35:32,110
you've publicly

786
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,170
embarrassed the Chief.

787
00:35:36,190 --> 00:35:38,030
From now on, your work in the village

788
00:35:38,030 --> 00:35:39,760
will be difficult to carry out.

789
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,320
Who could have guessed that
among those people

790
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:44,450
was his son-in-law?

791
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:45,480
Right?

792
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:49,280
We also didn't expect
Xiaoman to call the police directly.

793
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,680
This situation is messed up
all around now.

794
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,030
A cow's tail

795
00:35:53,030 --> 00:35:54,800
can only cover one cow's ass.

796
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,140
We can't worry about everything.

797
00:35:57,880 --> 00:36:01,070
Dealing with villagers is much harder
than archaeology.

798
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:02,530
That's absolutely right.

799
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,510
People who don't understand
our archaeological work

800
00:36:05,510 --> 00:36:07,670
think we’re just old scholars.

801
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,110
But once they interact with us,
they'll find out

802
00:36:10,110 --> 00:36:11,760
we’re also worldly people.

803
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:13,290
Dealing with villagers

804
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:16,000
means you have to study
human nature and social customs.

805
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:17,550
Sometimes, no matter how nicely you speak,

806
00:36:17,550 --> 00:36:19,960
it’s better to treat others
as you want to be treated.

807
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:21,090
That’s a big lesson.

808
00:36:21,630 --> 00:36:23,690
There’s a lot you still need to learn.

809
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,280
Lay the road on clear days,

810
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:28,010
don’t step in mud on rainy days.

811
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:31,820
I've learned a lot.

812
00:36:56,070 --> 00:36:56,670
Wen Wen.

813
00:36:57,580 --> 00:36:59,110
I'm very worried about you.

814
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:03,230
We’re both caught in the fire,

815
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,660
but people have to take responsibility.

816
00:37:06,670 --> 00:37:07,320
Come back,

817
00:37:07,890 --> 00:37:09,620
and we'll solve this together.

818
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:42,550
Wen Wen.

819
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,000
You're finally home.

820
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:46,980
I was worried sick.

821
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:50,880
You must have suffered a lot these days.

822
00:37:58,260 --> 00:37:58,990
Don't worry.

823
00:38:00,030 --> 00:38:00,760
Today, I

824
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:03,530
will definitely help you get revenge.

825
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:07,150
It's been so many days
since this happened.

826
00:38:07,710 --> 00:38:10,570
Why hasn't there been
any movement from Mu Jianhui?

827
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,200
It's not good that there's no movement?

828
00:38:14,150 --> 00:38:15,710
Recently, my heart

829
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:17,400
has been pounding every day.

830
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:19,680
I'm afraid Jianhui found out

831
00:38:19,700 --> 00:38:20,840
and got even with us.

832
00:38:24,590 --> 00:38:26,720
You didn't buy fake medicine, did you?

833
00:38:28,590 --> 00:38:29,400
That can't be.

834
00:38:32,210 --> 00:38:32,850
Who is it?

835
00:38:35,710 --> 00:38:36,190
Coming.

836
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:37,380
Coming.

837
00:38:38,110 --> 00:38:38,640
Who is it?

838
00:38:42,950 --> 00:38:43,960
You rascal.

839
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:44,630
What's wrong?

840
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:45,360
Stand still.

841
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:47,800
Where do you think you’re running?

842
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:48,400
No, no, no.

843
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:49,590
I'll beat you to death today!

844
00:38:49,590 --> 00:38:51,350
Stop hitting me. What are you doing?

845
00:38:51,350 --> 00:38:52,310
Run!

846
00:38:52,550 --> 00:38:54,280
-What’s wrong with you?
-What are you doing?

847
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:55,010
Stand still.

848
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:55,940
Don't move!

849
00:39:01,070 --> 00:39:02,070
Jianhui, stop hitting him.

850
00:39:02,070 --> 00:39:03,400
Why are you hitting me
without saying anything?

851
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,320
You know damn well what you've done.

852
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:07,320
I did this for you and my sister.

853
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:10,550
Otherwise, I wouldn't have done
such a disgusting thing.

854
00:39:10,550 --> 00:39:11,810
For me and your sister?

855
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:14,000
Look, my sister can't have children now.

856
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:16,150
The Mu family can’t be left
without descendants.

857
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:18,070
How will you and my sister
live the rest of your lives without kids?

858
00:39:18,070 --> 00:39:18,870
Liu Shusheng.

859
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:21,100
Is this the first day I met you?

860
00:39:22,710 --> 00:39:25,190
I know exactly what kind of
person you are.

861
00:39:25,710 --> 00:39:27,510
The Gunner's business is booming.

862
00:39:27,510 --> 00:39:28,920
He's taken over several big tombs.

863
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:30,110
You were jealous.

864
00:39:30,110 --> 00:39:31,150
You were holding in your anger.

865
00:39:31,150 --> 00:39:33,070
Coming up with such a despicable scheme.

866
00:39:33,070 --> 00:39:34,270
Stirring up trouble.

867
00:39:34,550 --> 00:39:36,150
You wanted to profit from it.

868
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:38,190
Heaven knows my heart!

869
00:39:38,190 --> 00:39:40,450
I really don't have such bad intentions.

870
00:39:40,670 --> 00:39:41,280
Look.

871
00:39:41,670 --> 00:39:43,280
You asked me to watch over our company.

872
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:45,070
I've been staying there obediently.

873
00:39:45,070 --> 00:39:45,800
I don't go anywhere else.

874
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,800
I'm there watching over it every day.

875
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,000
See how obedient I am?

876
00:39:51,250 --> 00:39:52,050
Don't do that!

877
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,280
Y-You... Don't get excited.

878
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:58,510
Right.

879
00:39:59,150 --> 00:40:01,070
Let me report to you

880
00:40:01,070 --> 00:40:02,110
about the company’s recent situation.

881
00:40:02,110 --> 00:40:02,840
Is that okay?

882
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:04,340
Our company...

883
00:40:05,030 --> 00:40:07,690
Now, the project is progressing
very smoothly.

884
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:09,740
The workers are doing a great job.

885
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:12,800
I specifically instructed
the engineering department.

886
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:14,030
I said, for this project,

887
00:40:14,030 --> 00:40:15,890
we absolutely can't cut corners.

888
00:40:16,190 --> 00:40:18,450
We must ensure the safety of the project.

889
00:40:20,210 --> 00:40:21,540
There's one more thing.

890
00:40:21,670 --> 00:40:23,190
A company

891
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:24,320
came by recently

892
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:26,200
looking to build a hotel.

893
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:27,810
What was its name again?

894
00:40:28,710 --> 00:40:29,480
Your slap just

895
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:30,630
made me forget everything.

896
00:40:30,630 --> 00:40:31,590
Mingda Hotel.

897
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,000
Right, right, right.

898
00:40:34,230 --> 00:40:35,160
How did you know?

899
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:41,330
You didn't send them, did you?

900
00:40:41,460 --> 00:40:42,910
How many projects have you built

901
00:40:42,910 --> 00:40:44,170
in the last six months?

902
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,160
In the past six months...

903
00:40:46,230 --> 00:40:47,480
Three? Maybe four?

904
00:40:47,590 --> 00:40:48,790
How many did you sign?

905
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:49,760
I signed...

906
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:51,800
Four or five?

907
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,150
You signed fifteen.

908
00:40:53,900 --> 00:40:56,420
But you only actually built two.

909
00:40:57,110 --> 00:40:58,110
As for the rest...

910
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:01,180
You'll never see them in Qinchuan
in your lifetime.

911
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:10,110
So

912
00:41:10,110 --> 00:41:11,550
our construction company
is just for money laundering?

913
00:41:11,550 --> 00:41:12,110
Shut up!

914
00:41:14,270 --> 00:41:16,730
Do you know how much money
is in your account?

915
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:17,570
Well...

916
00:41:18,170 --> 00:41:19,480
The accountant has always
been managing the accounts.

917
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,280
I haven't asked about it.

918
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:22,810
Forty-five million seven hundred thousand.

919
00:41:28,590 --> 00:41:29,960
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

920
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,690
Who knew you were such a person?

921
00:41:32,420 --> 00:41:33,820
Your head is full of mush.

922
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:42,440
I was wrong.

923
00:41:45,590 --> 00:41:46,990
If you're not satisfied,

924
00:41:47,190 --> 00:41:49,110
come on, slap me twice more.

925
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,730
It doesn't matter if I'm satisfied or not.

926
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:54,860
What about Wen Wen?

927
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,260
She's an unmarried woman.

928
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:02,880
Gunner doesn't know about this yet.

929
00:42:03,070 --> 00:42:04,150
If he finds out,

930
00:42:04,350 --> 00:42:06,550
you won't even have a whole corpse left.

931
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:07,950
Liu Shusheng,

932
00:42:08,630 --> 00:42:09,910
for the trouble you've caused,

933
00:42:09,910 --> 00:42:11,240
go apologize to Wen Wen.

934
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:14,560
If she forgives you,
we can work something out.

935
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,290
If she doesn't forgive you,

936
00:42:17,510 --> 00:42:18,970
none of us can go on living.

937
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,070
Wen Wen.

938
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:38,000
Wen Wen.

939
00:42:40,030 --> 00:42:41,110
I know I was wrong.

940
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:43,360
I should never have

941
00:42:43,550 --> 00:42:45,360
done such a conscienceless thing.

942
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,420
Please forgive me.

943
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:48,620
You've ruined my entire life.

944
00:42:48,950 --> 00:42:50,790
Wen Wen, I know you're angry.

945
00:42:52,190 --> 00:42:53,720
How can you feel better now?

946
00:42:54,030 --> 00:42:55,230
Do whatever you want.

947
00:42:55,550 --> 00:42:57,320
As long as it makes you
feel a little better,

948
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,880
you can do whatever you want.
